```java
public class Solution {
    public boolean isPowerOfThree(int n) {
        // Check if n is negative or zero
        if (n <= 0) {
            return false;
        }

        // Use Math.log() to calculate the base-3 logarithm
        double logValue = Math.log(n) / Math.log(3);

        // Check if the logarithm value is an integer
        return logValue == (int) logValue;
    }
}
```

This solution works because `Math.log(n) / Math.log(3)` calculates the base-3 logarithm of `n`. If `n` is a power of 3, then this expression will evaluate to an integer. Otherwise, it will evaluate to a non-integer. We use `(int) logValue` to cast the result to an integer and compare it with `logValue`. If they are equal, then `logValue` was an integer, and `n` is a power of 3.

